  "text": "Plugin signature verification in grafana/grafana is implemented through a multi-stage pipeline involving manifest signing, signature validation, and unsigned plugin allowlist enforcement.\n\n## Core Signature Verification Files\n\n**Manifest Signing and Verification (pkg/plugins/manager/signature/manifest.go):**\nThe `Signature` struct implements the `SignatureCalculator` interface and is responsible for reading and verifying plugin manifests. Key methods include:\n- `Calculate()`: Calculates the plugin's signature state by reading the manifest and verifying file hashes\n- `ReadPluginManifestFromFS()`: Reads the MANIFEST.txt file containing the plugin signature\n- `readPluginManifest()`: Decodes and parses the PGP-signed manifest\n- `validateManifest()`: Validates required manifest fields and verifies the PGP signature\n- `Verify()`: Performs PGP signature verification using OpenPGP libraries\n\nThe manifest structure (PluginManifest) contains plugin ID, version, signature type, signing organization, file hashes, and root URLs for private/community plugins.\n\n**Signature Validation on Load (pkg/plugins/manager/signature/signature.go):**\nThe `Validation` struct implements the `Validator` interface and handles signature validation at load time:\n- `ValidateSignature()`: Validates plugin signatures and handles signature inheritance for child plugins\n- Uses a `PluginLoaderAuthorizer` to check if unsigned plugins are allowed\n- Returns appropriate plugin errors for invalid, modified, or unsigned plugins\n\n**Unsigned Plugin Allowlist Enforcement (pkg/plugins/manager/signature/authorizer.go):**\nThe `UnsignedPluginAuthorizer` implements the `PluginLoaderAuthorizer` interface:\n- `CanLoadPlugin()`: Determines if an unsigned plugin can be loaded by checking:\n  1. Dev mode status (allows unsigned plugins in development)\n  2. Plugin ID against the `PluginsAllowUnsigned` configuration list\n  3. Returns true only if the plugin is in the allowlist or dev mode is enabled\n\n## Public Key Retrieval System\n\n**Static Key Retriever (pkg/plugins/manager/signature/statickey/static_retriever.go):**\nProvides a hardcoded Grafana public key for signature verification:\n- `GetPublicKey()`: Returns the static PGP public key for a given key ID\n- Falls back to this when dynamic key retrieval is disabled\n\n**Dynamic Key Retriever (pkg/services/pluginsintegration/keyretriever/dynamic/dynamic_retriever.go):**\nManages dynamic retrieval and caching of public keys from grafana.com API:\n- `GetPublicKey()`: Retrieves public keys from cache (kv storage)\n- `downloadKeys()`: Fetches plugin signing keys from the grafana.com API endpoint\n- Implements automatic key syncing every 10 days with cache validation\n- `ensureKeys()`: Initializes key storage with the default static key if empty\n\n**Key Retriever Service (pkg/services/pluginsintegration/keyretriever/retriever.go):**\nAggregates static and dynamic key retrieval:\n- `GetPublicKey()`: Routes to dynamic key retriever if enabled, otherwise uses static key\n\n## Validation Pipeline Integration\n\n**Validation Pipeline (pkg/plugins/manager/pipeline/validation/steps.go):**\nImplements the signature validation step in the plugin loading pipeline:\n- `SignatureValidationStep()`: Creates a ValidateFunc for signature validation\n- Integrates with the validation pipeline to check signatures before plugin initialization\n\n**Bootstrap Stage (pkg/plugins/manager/pipeline/bootstrap/steps.go):**\nCalculates signatures during the bootstrap phase:\n- `DefaultConstructor.Construct()`: Uses SignatureCalculator to calculate plugin signatures\n- Integrates manifest signing verification into the plugin construction process\n\n## Configuration and Settings\n\n**Plugin Configuration (pkg/plugins/config/config.go):**\nDefines the plugin management configuration structure:\n- `PluginsAllowUnsigned`: List of plugin IDs allowed to load without signatures\n- Passed to the UnsignedPluginAuthorizer for allowlist checking\n\n**Settings Reader (pkg/setting/setting_plugins.go):**\nReads plugin configuration from the Grafana config file:\n- Reads `allow_loading_unsigned_plugins` setting from the [plugins] section\n- Also reads key retrieval settings: `public_key_retrieval_disabled`, `public_key_retrieval_on_startup`\n\n## Core Interfaces\n\n**Key Interfaces (pkg/plugins/ifaces.go):**\n- `SignatureCalculator`: Interface for calculating plugin signatures during bootstrap\n- `PluginLoaderAuthorizer`: Interface for authorizing plugin loading based on signature status\n- `KeyRetriever`: Interface for retrieving public keys for signature verification\n\n## Pipeline Integration\n\n**Pipeline Setup (pkg/services/pluginsintegration/pipeline/pipeline.go):**\n- Integrates signature calculator into the bootstrap stage\n- Integrates signature validator into the validation stage\n- Wires together all components in the plugin loading pipeline\n\n**Wire Bindings (pkg/services/pluginsintegration/pluginsintegration.go):**\nDefines dependency injection bindings:\n- Binds `signature.Signature` to `SignatureCalculator`\n- Binds `signature.Validation` to the signature validator\n- Binds `signature.UnsignedPluginAuthorizer` to `PluginLoaderAuthorizer`\n- Binds `keyretriever.Service` to `KeyRetriever`\n\n## Data Models\n\n**Signature Status Constants (pkg/plugins/models.go):**\n- SignatureStatusValid: Signed and verified\n- SignatureStatusInvalid: Invalid signature\n- SignatureStatusModified: Valid signature but file contents modified\n- SignatureStatusUnsigned: No MANIFEST.txt file\n- SignatureStatusInternal: Core plugin with no signature\n\n## Signature Verification Flow\n\nThe complete flow is:\n1. During bootstrap, `Construct()` calls `SignatureCalculator.Calculate()`\n2. `Calculate()` reads MANIFEST.txt and verifies it's PGP-signed\n3. `validateManifest()` checks required fields and calls `Verify()` with the public key\n4. `Verify()` uses `KeyRetriever.GetPublicKey()` to get the public key (from dynamic API or static fallback)\n5. OpenPGP signature verification confirms the manifest wasn't tampered with\n6. File hashes in the manifest are verified against actual plugin files\n7. During validation, `ValidateSignature()` checks the signature status\n8. For unsigned plugins, `UnsignedPluginAuthorizer.CanLoadPlugin()` checks the allowlist\n9. Unsigned plugins not in the allowlist are prevented from loading\n"
